In many places it is saved on disinfectants
This year, more than a thousand cases of infection were registered in hospitals due to the inappropriate use of antibiotics.
Hygiene conditions of hospitals, overfilling beds, overloading of staff do not help to stop the diseases, according to the head of the National Epidemiological Center.
In many places, it also saves on disinfectants.
Recently, an MRSA infection was diagnosed in the trauma department of St. John's Hospital.
Antibiotic-resistant bacteria have been discovered in a man who got to the hospital after a serious car accident.
The patient was isolated.
A similar infection occurred in the same place at the beginning of the year.
The patient injured in a serious car accident was released home, but not long after that he had to return with an MRSA infection, and due to the bacteria located in his body, one important operation could not yet be performed.
By this year’s December 10, 1,094 hospital infections caused by multi-resistent disease agents were reported to the National Nesocomialis Surveillance system, Karolina Böröcz, head of the National Epidemico Center.
This means that so many infections caused by multi-resistant disease agents have been confidently registered in hospitals, others are not known.
Nearly two-thirds (683) of infections were caused by MRSA, or methicilin-oxiclin resistant golden staphylococcus.
Staphylococcus aureus (SA) bacteria are worn by a third of people in their noses without causing the disease.
Infections caused by SA (e.g. cervical inflammation, tonsilitis, leather infection, early infection) respond well to antibiotics and can be treated well.
However, if antibiotics are administered excessively or inappropriately, it develops from a bacterium that is very resistant to antibiotics and which is rapidly spread in inadequate hospital conditions.
Above all, in the case of temporarily or persistently poor functioning of the immune system in patients with a weakened organism, low body weight or patients in years, can cause serious hospital infections, such as early infection or blood poisoning – sepsis.
According to the Chief Physician of St. John's Hospital, there is nothing special about MRSA infection, a similar infection belongs to the daily practice in hospitals.
“Infection must not be confused with the epidemic, MRSA is not only there,” said Tibor Nyulasi, “where the presence of the causative agent of the disease is not investigated.”
Resistant to antibiotics
“We are isolating these patients, the nursing staff is treating them in rubber gloves and in the mask, and we have the necessary antibiotics for their treatment,” said Tibor Nyulasi.
Patients admitted to the hospital are first under investigation of whether it is present in their MRSA organism, but the infection cannot always be avoided.
Sampling is not in fashion
The vast majority of hospital infections caused by MRSA could be prevented, but the current conditions and conditions in domestic hospitals are not favorable for the prevention and spread of multidrug-resistant agents of diseases, according to Karolina Böröczová.
Since this infection occurs characteristically in hospitals and homes for the elderly, hospitals should check patients' admitted patients and isolate MRSA carriers immediately.
However, the collection of microbiological samples in Hungarian hospitals is not in vogue.
This is also due to the fact that the National Health Insurance Fund does not finance these examinations.
Most cases are thus detected when the patient suffers from a perceptible MRSA infection, said the head of the epidemiological center.
The European Union has strict recommendations for appropriate antibiotic treatment in human medicine, and there are also domestic guidelines for the treatment of individual infections, medical history.
It is necessary to make it necessary to ensure that antibiotic therapy is targeted, or microbiological examinations should be carried out in order to prevent resistance from drugs, but even hospitals do not comply with this in all cases.
Sampling of microbiological samples is even rare even rare in the basic or outpatient treatment of patients, Karolina Böröczová said.
The Recipients Are Disinfected
According to scientific evidence, MRSA spreads among patients most often through medical staff.
Therefore, it plays a very important role to wash hands and the use of gloves and masks, but even in this, there are serious shortcomings in hospitals.
MRSA is transmitted by droplet infection and touch, but in the conditions of domestic hospitals it is not always possible to isolate the infected patients.
Rooms, on the other hand, are often overcrowded, beds are often very close to each other, although from an epidemiological point of view, patients should be at least 1.5 meters apart.
As Karolina Böröcz noted, we can also encounter the fact that there are few in hospitals in unfavorable material situation, there are few patients, and many patients, which increases the chances of infection.
According to Karolina Böröczová, where the necessary protective measures are followed, similar infections are demonstrably less or the further spread of the disease cause can be stopped.
Government program against MRSA
The treatment of MRSA infection is a huge expense for health insurance companies, so it is being fought against everywhere.
In England, for example, the government has drafted a MRSA prevention program, or a decrease in its incidence.
As the program seems to be successful, according to published data, the MRSA infections in England show a decreasing trend.
The European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC) ranks among its priorities for the prevention of multi-resistent disease agents (including MRSA) or hospital infections caused by these disease agents.
