A huge strike is coming
The League unions, or the National Union of Workers' Councils (MoIZ), will on Friday create its strike commission to coordinate Monday's unlimited strike.
On Saturday, a protest public gathering is held, on Monday – on the day of the final vote on the Health Insurance Act – work will be stopped.
The event will certainly cause serious traffic disruptions, because the railway transport will almost completely stop and within 13 hours employees of the Budapest transport company (BKV) will also strike.
On Friday afternoon, the League Association will acquaint the League with the National Union of Workers' Councils with the details of the jointly organized Monday strike.
There will also be a strike committee of the LEAG – MOSZ, which will coordinate Monday’s action.
A protest public gathering is held on Saturday, and from Monday, unions joining the strike will stop work indefinitely, unless there is an agreement with the government.
This means that no deadline for an end to the strike has been set, which will begin on the day of the parliamentary vote on the Health Insurance Act.
If the Parliament did not eventually adopt the Health Insurance Act, the unions will immediately withdraw the call for the strike.
However, if the legislation is voted on, the strike committees will meet and decide on the next steps.
According to Monday's agenda for the Parliamentary Meeting, it is also possible that the Health Insurance Act will be voted on only in the late evening or night hours.
Due to the Monday start-up strike, it is possible to count on serious traffic interruptions: at the railway station, the work will be stopped for an indefinite period of time, in the morning part of Budapest's public transport and more than half of Volan companies can stop.
At the same time, half of the lane will also be closed in many parts of the country.
Numerous unions and civil organizations have joined the call for the strike, the list of which is constantly updated on the League Association website.
Some organizations announced a strike indefinitely, others declared a temporary cessation of work.
By Thursday afternoon, the Hungarian State Railways (MÁV) and the Independent Union of Railway Employees (VDSZSZ) were unable to agree on sufficient services, while more and more people are travelling on the railway station at the beginning of the Christmas holidays.
According to the previous reports, the BKV will strike from the beginning of operation within 13 hours, from 7 a.m. to 9 a.m. at Budapest Airport, a four-hour strike will be held by the Union of Employees in the LIGA Energy Industry, and the 2-8-hour cessation of work was called by the Union of Educators and the Democratic Union of Educators.
The Union of Hungarian Physicians will strike alternately across the country, the Democratic Union of Healthcare Workers and the Social Workers (EDDSZ), belonging to the Cooperation Forum of Trade Unions (SZEF), is holding a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands formulated by the League association is that the government recalls the draft health insurance reform and submit a new concept for a public discussion.
The second requirement is that the new method of counting pensioners valid from next year is gradually introduced.
Third, in order to ensure the pre-initiative of the early retirement for the relevant fields of work, the scope of inclusion in the system before 2010.
The fourth reason for the action is that the Independent Trade Union of Railway Employees (VDSZSZ), under the League Trade Union Association, does not accept the offer of the Ministry of Economy and Transport concerning railway branches, and expects a different offer.
