What insurance is appropriate for me?
Car insurance that protects the driver in the event of an accident. constitutes a significant expenditure, which depends on various factors, such as age, status, gender, the length of possession of a driving licence, the type of vehicle to be insured or used, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing a suitable car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured person.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the insurance company will receive an agreed insurance amount in a certain amount for taking charge of the payment of damages in the event of an insured event.
Insurance is the price of insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors, such as age, status, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, type of vehicle that is insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the more likely there is to be a crash, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both persons over the age of 25 and women must pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of the checks, insurance companies have concluded that those living in marriage tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of journeys and thus the likelihood of having an accident.
The increase in the frequency of rides increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when they set the price of insurance premiums.
Therefore, the driver must well study the situation in order to choose the insurance that best corresponds to his profile of the insured.
Here we will show the most important variables for choosing one or another type of insurance, which, in addition to complying with the type of insured, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five encounter different disadvantages such as little driving experience and short possession of a driver's license when they want to arrange premiums at an affordable price.
Although the best for good coverage is insurance against all risks, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks with a discount of premiums in order to obtain insurance coverage of all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would assume the participation of the client in the payment of an insured event.
"Part of the payment of the insured event provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the price of the premium, which will be all the higher than that which would be the lower the deductible," explains Luis Noguera, Head of First Europe, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants of the operation so that the client insures himself against damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and the loss of the vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as much as possible, as it will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce premiums in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
Malus, on the other hand, is an increase in the base rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profit.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus,” Noguera explains.
After crossing the limit of twenty-five years, drivers have it easier when they go to take out insurance, because the client’s risk index is reduced, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to take out insurance against all risks at a discount.
“Young people usually cannot use the experience of the pre-acquired when there is a crash, nor in the management,” assures the director of a European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of the proceedings, when the “fear of a newcomer” has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies to be the clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a discount of premiums (which could be €300) or at a high bonus, insurance extended to other business participants, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
“Their management is calmer and their purchasing capacity higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount,” notes Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to insure against all risks with a discount of premiums (which is 150 euros) or insurance extended to other business participants if a high bonus has been achieved.
It should be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is a strong reason for properly studying the possibilities of insurance that would suit us best in relation to our personal situation.
